Prop. 28. In equal circles equal straight lines (equal
                    chords) cut off equal arcs, the greater equal to the greater,
                    and the less equal to the less;

The proof is simply this. As α = δ we know that ma≈mb;
                    therefore if ma>nc, then mb>nc, if ma - nc, then mb=nc, if ma<fnc, then mb<fnc, therefore the first
                    proportion holds by Definition 5.

For the row consists of a line and all the points in it, reciprocal to it
                    therefore will be a line with all planes through it, that is, an axial pencil;
                    and so for the other cases.

§ 61. Any two tangents to a parabola are cut by all others in projective rows;
                    but the line at infinity being one of the tangents, the points at infinity on
                    the rows are corresponding points, and the rows therefore similar. Hence—
